description: The `synthetic.web_analytics_pageviews` table represents pageview records for a web analytics system, capturing individual page view events within user sessions. The table is uniquely identified by `pageview_id` and includes details such as `session_id`, `page_url`, `page_title`, `timestamp`, `time_on_page_seconds`, and `referrer`, allowing analysis of how users interact with web content. While this table lacks defined foreign key relationships, its role is likely central to tracking user engagement per session on web pages.

columns.name: pageview_id
columns.description: This column uniquely identifies each individual pageview event within the web analytics system. It is used to track and differentiate user interactions with web pages consistently.

columns.name: session_id
columns.description: This column represents a unique identifier for each user session on the website, ensuring that page views within the same session can be tracked together. Each number corresponds to a different session, allowing for analysis of user engagement patterns.

columns.name: page_url
columns.description: This column represents the URLs of web pages that have been viewed by users. It includes a mix of domain names and protocols, indicating the use of both secure (HTTPS) and non-secure (HTTP) connections to various websites.

columns.name: page_title
columns.description: This column likely represents the titles assigned to web pages that are visited and recorded in analytics, reflecting a variety of contexts, such as events, relationships, and environmental themes. Purpose unclear from available data.

columns.name: timestamp
columns.description: This column records the date and time when a pageview occurs on a website, adjusted for Central Daylight Time. Purpose unclear from available data.

columns.name: time_on_page_seconds
columns.description: This column represents the duration in seconds that a user spent on a webpage during a single visit. These values can help assess user engagement with online content.

columns.name: referrer
columns.description: Purpose unclear from available data. The column appears to store fragmented phrases or sentences with no evident pattern or meaning.

columns.name: created_at
columns.description: This column captures the date and time when a web page view event was recorded in the system. It defaults to the current timestamp at the moment of record creation, indicating when the view occurred.

columns.name: updated_at
columns.description: This column captures the precise moment when each record on webpage views was most recently updated or modified. Purpose unclear from available data regarding the nature or source of these updates.

indexes.index_definition: CREATE UNIQUE INDEX web_analytics_pageviews_pkey ON synthetic.web_analytics_pageviews USING btree (pageview_id)
